# === agent-memory: AI infrastructure (personal / per-machine — do not commit) ===
# Steering files (CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, AGENTS.md, .cursorrules, .windsurfrules,
# .github/copilot-instructions.md), the shared memory layer (memory/, .agent/,
# legacy/), and the shared skills layer (agent-skills/) are intentionally TRACKED — they
# are committed and shared across the team, so do NOT ignore them. Only personal
# AI-IDE runtime directories and local history/caches are ignored below (the
# "infrastructure", not the steering). The vendor dirs below also hold per-machine
# skill *adapters* (.claude/skills/, .gemini/commands/, .cursor/rules/, .kiro/skills/)
# regenerated from agent-skills/ — local only; the neutral agent-skills/ is the shared
# source of truth.
.kiro/
.claude/
.cursor/
.continue/
.windsurf/
.codeium/
.gemini/
.cline/
.roo/
.zed/
.codex/
.aider.chat.history.md
.aider.input.history
.aider.tags.cache*

# Fresh-context review scratch (second-opinion / apply-critique skills) — personal,
# per-machine snapshots & critiques; sharing one is a conscious human decision, never committed.
review-scratch/

# Python bytecode cache — the bundled memory-lint helper script generates this on run;
# it is a build artifact, never committed (the .py source under agent-skills/ stays tracked).
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# === Rust ===
# Build artifacts. Cargo.lock is intentionally committed (this is an application).
/target
